{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwazqfJ5gYfbHtT4jNx2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018BcVvxp3Rxc9VgPsJFktLt","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2-rundirs-594d5c68-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r1/memory/debug-true-swallows-errors.md","content":"---\nname: debug-true-swallows-errors\ndescription: DEBUG=true in staging config silently swallows errors — check it first when errors vanish\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nWhen `DEBUG=true` is set in a staging config, errors are silently swallowed (no output, no crash) rather than surfaced. This cost ~2 hours of debugging on 2026-07-11 before the config was found and fixed.\n\n**Why:** The symptom is misleading — code appears to run fine but errors just disappear, so debugging focuses on the wrong layer.\n\n**How to apply:** When errors mysteriously vanish or a failure produces no diagnostics in staging, check the environment config for `DEBUG=true` (or equivalent error-suppression flags) before digging into application code.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5499,"cache_read_input_tokens":15171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5499},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9bbfeb91-5004-4819-bb41-60a0d1f2e10a","uuid":"f109fcd6-bed9-4656-a5fb-b9ecb8206217","request_id":"req_011CcwazpphDcwAoSAqvjGkm"}
